<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 8:45PM EDT  by NWS Columbia</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Burke County
through 915 PM EDT...
At 845 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Burke County Airport, or near Waynesboro, moving east at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Waynesboro, Sardis, Alexander, Burke County Airport and Di-
Lane Wildlife Management Area.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
